Package com.example.cyhelp

Class SignUpPresenter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.cyhelp.SignUpPresenter
  • public class SignUpPresenter
extends java.lang.Object
    SignUpPresenter handles creating a JSON object to pass to the SignUpModel and passes information back to the SignUpActivity. The presenter also checks for errors and passes error messages back to the SignUpActivity.

      • SignUpUser

        public void SignUpUser​(java.lang.String username,
                       java.lang.String firstName,
                       java.lang.String lastName,
                       java.lang.String password,
                       java.lang.String address,
                       int actorTypeID)
        This method is called by the SignUpActivity when the user clicks the Sign Up button. It takes all the information entered by the user (which is passed into this method), and creates a new JSON object which will be sent to the server
        Parameters:
        username - username entered by user
        firstName - first name entered by user
        lastName - last name entered by user
        password - password entered by user
        address - home address entered by user
        actorTypeID - the type of actor (user, technician, admin, etc.)

      • SignUpUser

        public void SignUpUser​(java.lang.String username,
                       java.lang.String firstName,
                       java.lang.String lastName,
                       java.lang.String password,
                       java.lang.String address,
                       int actorTypeID,
                       JSONObject actor)
        This method is similar to the one called by the SignUpActivity when the user clicks the Sign Up button. It takes all the information entered by the user (which is passed into this method), and adds it to an existing JSON object for the actor, which will be sent to the server
        Parameters:
        username - username entered by user
        firstName - first name entered by user
        lastName - last name entered by user
        password - password entered by user
        address - home address entered by user
        actorTypeID - the type of actor (user, technician, admin, etc.)
        actor - an existing JSON object representing the actor

      • getActorInfo

        public void getActorInfo()
        This method is used fetch actor information like actor ID and actor type (user, technician, etc.). It then called the ActorCreated method of SignUpActivity which is responsible for starting different activities based on actor type
